<br>
I am not sure if you ever played the original Diablo online, but it is a perfect example of why we should all care about the games integrity. In that game someone created a trainer (Hence the name Raymond’s Diablo Trainer) that was distributed for free to everyone. This trainer made it possible to become invincible, easily duplicate any item in the game and always have full health and Mana, among other things. Once this was out the game became all but unplayable. Every single person had the best possible item on in every slot, cash meant nothing, in fact there was really no need to even loot anything. I have a feeling the creators of Everquest also played Diablo, luckily. <br>
<br>
The creators of EQ have always taken dup bugs more seriously then just about anything else. That is why (I believe the offer is still valid) in the past if you were able to find a Dup bug that you could reproduce and reported it you would be gifted with (I can’t remember all the options) an in game title of your choosing, have your account marked free permanently and other amazing rewards. <br>
<br>
Once the game is trivialized like that playing it becomes pointless. The one thing that makes this game so great is we all know that everyone (for the most part) has had to earn the levels and equipment they have (Save ShowEq_gimp01). While you can buy a character off Ebay, you cannot buy the skills and experience it takes to get a character to level 60+. <br>
<br>
Remove the risk of the game and you remove the fun. <br>
<br>
Anyway, the reason you should not try to duplicate this or any other bug is because the risk of getting banned is just not worth the reward. Think about how badly you would feel if you were caught and got banned. If you want to test things out for yourself, in the name of getting something fixed, just follow the steps Amel provided. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 339<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 12:40:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=454.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freesehttp://pages.prodigy.net/cohmsford/america.gifrvers.com/images/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bug abuse</span><hr size=1> How does ShowEQ keep you from gaining game skill? At this point it's basically zonewide track and that's it..<br>
